Earlier context
The CloudOven payment infrastructure went through significant iteration: initial M-Pesa Daraja integration was built and partially hardened (duplicate STK push prevention, idempotent finalization, sandbox STK push confirmed working on device), but Safaricom's requirement to switch settlement to bank account led Allan to pivot to IntaSend as the payment aggregator. The backend was rewritten accordingly, with intasend_transactions as the canonical payments table. A security incident occurred when credentials were exposed in chat; Allan rotated them immediately. The CloudOven stack was confirmed as React/Vite on Vercel, Node/Express on Render, Supabase PostgreSQL, and IntaSend for M-Pesa.
